# 5. 書かれていない想い

???: (Again...)
???: (Again, from the beginning.)
???: (Until you get it right.)
???: (Otherwise, you'll be seen as a failure.)
???: (Mom... Dad... Everyone has such high hopes for me...)
???: (But...)
???: (How long do I have to keep doing this?)
???: (When am I going to satisfy their expectations?)
???: (I...)
???: (I...don't think I ever can...)
???: ...
???: Is this really it for you...?
Toya: *Gasp*
Toya: It was a dream...?
Toya: (I feel like that's all I've been seeing lately...)
Toya: (I keep getting thrown back to that time. All these wounds are opening back up...)
Toya: (No, I don't have time to be dealing with those things right now...)
Toya: (I have to keep working... I have to complete at least one song...)
Toya's Mother's Voice: Toya...?
Toya: Oh, Mom...
Toya: Is something wrong?
Toya's Mother: You're up again early today...
Toya's Mother: I was worried that you haven't been getting enough sleep since you've been staying up so late recently.
Toya: Th-Thank you... But I'm...
Toya's Mother: I know what you're working on means quite a lot to you, Toya.
Toya's Mother: But it'd be all for naught if it took a heavy toll on your health. Why don't you take a little break...?
Toya: But...
Toya: Yes, you're right... Then, I'll try going for a walk.
Toya's Mother: You will...? Please be careful, okay?
Toya: I will.
Toya: (I feel terrible about making her worry so much...)
Toya: (But I don't have a second to spare. I need to keep working on this song.)
Toya: (So, if I can't work at home, then I should go to...)
Toya: Alright...
Toya: (I'll continue working at MEIKO's place. I may even be able to ask KAITO for help if he's there.)
Toya: *Wince*
Toya: This isn't good... I feel dizzy and sleep-deprived...
Toya: No, I don't have time to rest... Not now. Not here...
???: Toya?
Toya: That voice...
Toya: MEIKO...
MEIKO: Why are you squatted down like that? Are you by chance not feeling well?
Toya: No, this is nothing... I just need to take a short break and... *Wince*
MEIKO: No. I can't just let you wallow in pain.
MEIKO: Sit tight. I'll go get you a drink from the cafe.
Toya: No, you don't have to...
MEIKO: Toya, do as I say.
Toya: Okay, I'll sit tight...
Toya: Phew...
Toya: Thank you very much. I feel much better after having some of your tea and snacks.
MEIKO: Thank goodness. Looks like you were just sleep-deprived.
MEIKO: If you're feeling better, then you should go back and get some real rest. Please stop by after you've had a chance to recover.
Toya: I will. Again, I'm sorry for all the trouble I've caused you.
MEIKO: This was nothing.
MEIKO: But I don't feel great about how you've been pushing yourself so hard...
MEIKO: Is your song giving you that much trouble...?
Toya: Yes...
Toya: Every time I feel like I've got it right, I realize that I'm still nowhere near achieving the energy Ken and his team produced.
Toya: And no matter how much I think about it, I can't figure out why...
MEIKO: ...
MEIKO: Then, what if you went back to square one?
Toya: Square one...?
MEIKO: Yes. Back to the moment when you started working on this song.
MEIKO: Remember how you took down notes about the others' feelings?
Toya: Oh, yes... I have it right here actually.
MEIKO: Then, why don't you take another look at it?
MEIKO: I believe it's best to go back to where you started when you can't find the answer to a question.
Toya: I see...
Toya: (Lately, all I've been thinking about is why I haven't been able to achieve that same energy. I just kept looking for whatever it was that I was missing.)
Toya: (But going back to the beginning may allow me to see it with a fresh pair of eyes.)
Toya: Thank you. I'll try doing that.
MEIKO: Also, Toya, would you mind if I had a look at your notes?
Toya: What?
MEIKO: You showed them to KAITO already, right? I'm actually a little curious myself as to what you wrote...
Toya: Yes, of course. I'm sure the others would also be okay with it.
MEIKO: So, when you all performed in STAY GOLDEN that second time, Kohane decided to believe in herself because An believed in her.
Toya: Yes, that was what stood out to her the most. And I'd like to weave what she felt that time into my song...
MEIKO: Hehe. I'm looking forward to hearing what that sounds like.
MEIKO: Still, this notebook... It's really full of everyone's thoughts and feelings.
Toya: Yes. I was under the impression that these notes would help me come up with a good song...
Toya: But things just aren't going that way...
MEIKO: Hey, Toya.
MEIKO: Your notes went into great detail regarding how Kohane, An and Akito feel.
MEIKO: But there were only a few tidbits about you.
Toya: Huh? Oh, you're right...
Toya: But I already know how I feel, so I don't think I need to spell it all out in words...
MEIKO: Are you sure? Your feelings are also going to play a major role in your song, no?
MEIKO: So, what if you do for yourself what you did for the others? Try writing down everything that you've felt until now.
Toya: Everything I've felt...?
???: (I...)
???: (I...don't think I ever can...)
Toya: *Wince*
MEIKO: Toya?
Toya: Oh... Sorry. It's nothing.
MEIKO: Really? Are you sure you're feeling better...?
Toya: No, I do feel better. It's just...
Toya: Whenever I think about my feelings, I'm reminded of quite a lot of other things.
MEIKO: Other things?
Toya: Yes... Things that I'm not entirely proud of...
MEIKO: Then, why don't you try reflecting on those things...?
Toya: What?
MEIKO: You don't seem like you want to talk about whatever this subject matter is.
MEIKO: What if that's what's keeping you from completing your song?
Toya: Yes... If I'm going to incorporate the others' feelings, then I'll need to take a closer look at my own as well...
Toya: Thank you, MEIKO...
Toya: I'll try doing that today after I get back.
MEIKO: Okay. Good luck, Toya!
MEIKO: But please try to get some rest first. I wouldn't want you to start feeling dizzy again.
Toya: I will. And thank you for the concern.
